HEADWORD: Fidejussion
<hw>Fi`de*jus"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fidejussio</ets>, from <ets>fidejubere</ets> to be surety or bail;
<ets>fides</ets> faith + <ets>jubere</ets> to order: cf. F.
<ets>fid⟦eacute⟧jussion</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Civil Law)</fld> <def>The
act or state of being bound as surety for another; suretyship.</def>⟦br⟧
